{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "dra:proverbs.25",
    "translationId": "dra",
    "bookSlug": "proverbs",
    "chapterNumber": 25,
    "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 25",
    "summary": "Source text for Proverbs 25 in Douay-Rheims Bible (Challoner)."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.25.1",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 25,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 25:1",
      "text": "These are also parables of Solomon, which the men of Ezechias, king of Juda, copied out.",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.25.2",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 25,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 25:2",
      "text": "It is the glory of God to conceal the word, and the glory of kings to search out the speech.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.25.3",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 25,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 25:3",
      "text": "The heaven above and the earth beneath, and the heart of kings is unsearchable.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.25.4",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 25,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 25:4",
      "text": "Take away the rust from silver, and there shall come forth a most pure vessel:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.25.5",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 25,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 25:5",
      "text": "Take away wickedness from the face of the king, and his throne shall be established with justice.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.25.6",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 25,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 25:6",
      "text": "Appear not glorious before the king, and stand not in the place of great men.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.25.7",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 25,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 25:7",
      "text": "For it is better that it should be said to thee: Come up hither; than that thou shouldst be humbled before the prince.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.25.8",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 25,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 25:8",
      "text": "The things which thy eyes have seen, utter not hastily in a quarrel: lest afterward thou mayst not be able to make amends, when thou hast dishonoured thy friend.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.25.9",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 25,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 25:9",
      "text": "Treat thy cause with thy friend, and discover not the secret to a stranger:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.25.10",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 25,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 25:10",
      "text": "Lest he insult over thee, when he hath heard it, and cease not to upbraid thee. Grace and friendship deliver a man: keep these for thyself, lest thou fall under reproach.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.25.11",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 25,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 25:11",
      "text": "To speak a word in due time, is like apples of gold on beds of silver.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.25.12",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 25,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 25:12",
      "text": "As an earring of gold and a bright pearl, so is he that reproveth the wise, and the obedient ear.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.25.13",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 25,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 25:13",
      "text": "As the cold of snow in the time of harvest, so is a faithful messenger to him that sent him, for he refresheth his soul.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.25.14",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 25,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 25:14",
      "text": "As clouds, and wind, when no rain followeth, so is the man that boasteth, and doth not fulfil his promises.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.25.15",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 25,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 25:15",
      "text": "By patience a prince shall be appeased, and a soft tongue shall break hardness.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.25.16",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 25,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 25:16",
      "text": "Thou hast found honey, eat what is sufficient for thee, lest being glutted therewith thou vomit it up.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.25.17",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 25,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 25:17",
      "text": "Withdraw thy foot from the house of thy neighbour, lest having his fill he hate thee.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.25.18",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 25,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 25:18",
      "text": "A man that beareth false witness against his neighbour, is like a dart and a sword and a sharp arrow.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.25.19",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 25,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 25:19",
      "text": "To trust in an unfaithful man in the time of trouble, is like a rotten tooth, and weary foot,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.25.20",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 25,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 25:20",
      "text": "And one that looseth his garment in cold weather. As vinegar upon nitre, so is he that singeth songs to a very evil heart. As a moth doth by a garment, and a worm by the wood: so the sadness of a man consumeth the heart.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.25.21",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 25,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 25:21",
      "text": "If thy enemy be hungry, give him to eat: if he thirst, give him water to drink:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.25.22",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 25,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 25:22",
      "text": "For thou shalt heap hot coals upon his head, and the Lord will reward thee.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.25.23",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 25,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 25:23",
      "text": "The north wind driveth away rain, as doth a sad countenance a backbiting tongue.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.25.24",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 25,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 25:24",
      "text": "It is better to sit in a corner of the housetop: than with a brawling woman, and in a common house.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.25.25",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 25,
      "verseNumber": 25,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 25:25",
      "text": "As cold water to a thirsty soul, so are good tidings from a far country.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.25.26",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 25,
      "verseNumber": 26,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 25:26",
      "text": "A just man falling down before the wicked, is as a fountain troubled with the foot and a corrupted spring.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.25.27",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 25,
      "verseNumber": 27,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 25:27",
      "text": "As it is not good for a man to eat much honey, so he that is a searcher of majesty shall be overwhelmed by glory.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:proverbs.25.28",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 25,
      "verseNumber": 28,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 25:28",
      "text": "As a city that lieth open and is not compassed with walls, so is a man that cannot refrain his own spirit in speaking.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
